Use some common sense (and/or your business knowledge) to answer the first question. Which columns or (independent) variables would significantly influence the Y value (whether someone fulfills the terms of credit agreement or not)? List at least three and explain why?¶

Name the column (variable) and explain why?¶

CHK_ACCT is a column or (independent) variable that would significantly influence the Y value because people with more accounts are able to pay back loans more quickly as they are better able to manage their money

Name the column (variable) and explain why?¶

DURATION is a column or (independent) variable that would significantly influence the Y value because the longer the duration the less likely the person is going to pay back the full amount

Name the column (variable) and explain why?¶

AMOUNT is a column or (independent) variable that would significantly influence the Y value because the higher the amount the less likely the person is going to pay back the full amount as it will have a longer duration

Be very specific. What are the characteristics of the people who have paid back? Be very specific. What are the characteristics of the people who have defaulted on loans?¶

Provide a discussion of the overall findings in a markdown. This is the storytelling of this project, so you need to format this markdown (see https://github.com/adam-p/markdown-here/wiki/MarkdownHere-Cheatsheet). Use bulleted and/or numbered lists¶

Characteristics of people who have repaid their loans:

  • Borrow small-amount loans
  • Borrow for short-term durations
  • Have 2 or more checking accounts
  • Maintain highly skilled jobs
  • Have a good credit history

Characteristics of people who have defaulted on their loans:

  • Borrow large-amount loans
  • Borrow for long-term durations
  • Have less than 2 checking accounts
  • Maintain unskilled jobs
  • Have a poor credit history
